Author : Eric Bachard 
July 5th 2017

In this directory, you'll find everything to create a Linux Kiwi8 version.


Supposing you are using Debian like distribution,
here are the dependencies (means "YOU MUST" install what follows ...) :

- OpenGL lib + headers  // ImGui
- GLU + headers : freeglut3  // ImGui
- gtk-3.0 // nativefiledialog
- SDL2 
- glib-2.0
- pango
- cairo
- + all the mandatory gnome stuff (pfff ...)

In one command line :

sudo apt-get install libgtk-3-0 libgtk-3-bin libgtk-3-dev freeglut3 freeglut3-dev libsdl2-dev \
libsdl2-2.0-0 libsdl2-image-2.0-0 libsdl2-image-dev libatk-bridge2.0-0 libatk-bridge2.0-dev \
libpango1.0-0 libpango1.0-dev libpangocairo-1.0-0 libglib2.0-dev 

